text:
I am diabetic. I take Ozempic.  I do not take it for weight loss (and, sadly, it's never had that effect on me). I take it because I need it to stabilize my blood sugar.  I had stopped taking Ozempic and resorted to importing Semaglutide Peptides due to the crippling costs (more than $275 per month). Due to some hospital stays last year, I had maxed out my medical benefits (which meant that everything was 100% covered, not that I  ran out of benefits).  Over last year, I was able to get six months of meds free. I was dreading this year due to the prices I would need to pay.  

A couple days ago, I renewed my prescription and was delighted to discover that my $275+ per month had dropped to $25 per month, thanks to Trump's drug initiative. I didn't even have to hunt down coupons or anything.  I use Express Scripts and they just gave me the price of $25 per month (I get a 3 month supply, so it was a $75 charge).  $25 is cheaper than even the cost of imported Semaglutide Peptides. 

I am telling everyone about this amazing real-pocketbook savings of $2400 per year that Trump has saved me ON ONE DRUG (my three others were similarly inexpensive, but not as dramatic a price difference).  All told, Trump's prescription price changes will likely save me around $3000 per year. 

Thank you, Donald Trump.  Real world savings. Real world impact.  Real benefits to me due to his wisdom, his caring and his drive to place not just America first - but placing the AMERICAN PEOPLE first.
